HEADWORD: gosmore
<hw>gosmore</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A European weed
(<spn>Hypochaeris radicata</spn>) widely naturalized in North America
having yellow flower heads and leaves resembling a cat's ears.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cat's-ear, cat's ear, California dandelion,
capeweed, <spn>Hypochaeris radicata</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gospel</ent>⟦br⟧
